cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for classification using stacked autoencoders and random vector functional link (RVFL) networks. The paper focuses on improving the performance of RVFL networks by introducing direct connections between layers and denoising criteria in the autoencoders. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
